         </p>
         <list type="unordered">
             <item>
                 <p>if you point to an internal anchor in a <att>xml:id</att> inside the document you are working with, use # to begin with.</p>
             </item>
             <item>
                 <p>If you point to an external id don't start with #, just enter the ID. That is why
                     <gi>witness</gi> does not take that, as
                     <att>active</att>,
                     <att>passive</att> inside
                     <gi>relation</gi> should not. In fact you want
                     to be able to point to anchors within the records you are pointing
                     to and link things like LIT0000Example#t3.</p>
             </item>
         </list>
